Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:04.52,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,There are different kinds of memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.96,0:00:07.42,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,First of all, there’s one’s memory of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.72,0:00:10.04,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,You know what self-understanding is?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.56,0:00:14.04,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,You know that you are a girl named Lain with a certain face and height and weight?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.42,0:00:16.96,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,That’s all recorded at a molecular level.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.20,0:00:22.90,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Aside from the brain, there are places throughout the body that carry residues of things that have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.48,0:00:29.16,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,You know that if you get cut, you bleed, but if you wait a while, it scabs over and heals?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.84,0:00:33.66,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,That has to do with information stored in cells going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.80,0:00:38.76,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Take a look at athletes and people who have gone through intense physical training.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.80,0:00:40.86,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,They seem to do things effortlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.26,0:00:44.54,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,That’s because their bodies have their own recollection or memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.14,0:00:48.02,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,If you generate a recording, you have a memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.54,0:00:52.84,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,You might be able to say that sometimes, but not always.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.12,0:00:55.42,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Humans are haphazard and unpredictable, aren’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.52,0:00:58.98,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I don’t remember everything that happened to me as a kid precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.56,0:01:05.12,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I have happy memories of times I spent with my family, but my family might not have happy memories of those times at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.38,0:01:10.80,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I may have had misperceptions in the moment, or I may have remembered things incorrectly and by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.70,0:01:16.10,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,But we all walk around with memories, thinking that what we remember is what actually happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.78,0:01:19.68,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Suppose you meet an old friend that you haven’t seen in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.82,0:01:25.00,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Don’t you remember the things you used to do with that person right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.86,0:01:30.98,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Your memory has a way of linking things together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.72,0:01:33.88,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,If you can’t link things together, you’re sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.76,0:01:37.70,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Well, there is something called memory impediment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.70,0:01:43.02,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,People who have this can’t remember things that happened only moments ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.18,0:01:45.00,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,They have no idea of how things in the past took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.02,0:01:47.16,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,They don’t know what happened and in what order.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.16,0:01:52.02,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Since they don’t want anyone to know that they don’t remember things, they often make up stories about the past to fool people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.02,0:01:54.34,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Humans are complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.34,0:01:55.70,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,We do all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.46,0:02:00.60,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,You’ve seen senile old people on TV shows, haven’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.28,0:02:05.10,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,As humans, there are some things we can’t do anything about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.90,0:02:07.48,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Things we can’t do anything about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.60,0:02:10.80,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I’m not saying that you’re sick, Lain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.06,0:02:13.90,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,There are things we can’t do anything about, aren’t there?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.44,0:02:16.42,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,We can’t flap our arms and fly, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.96,0:02:19.62,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,There are memories in the body and the brain?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.98,0:02:23.60,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,There are still many things we don’t understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.02,0:02:29.36,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,The human brain is made up of many different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.22,0:02:36.46,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,When something is recorded there, there is a change that takes place that becomes the foundation for memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.14,0:02:38.46,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I don’t understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.24,0:02:40.54,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.54,0:02:44.34,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,When you go to high school and college, you can study up on all this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.86,0:02:47.54,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,But it’s good that you have a healthy curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:51.32,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I don’t think you’re sick, Lain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.20,0:02:55.68,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I feel that my memories aren’t my memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.28,0:02:59.70,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Sure! I feel that way sometimes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.02,0:03:04.04,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Even when it’s me. But I don’t remember anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.14,0:03:07.94,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,You’ve just forgotten something, that’s all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.96,0:03:10.66,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Didn’t I say that human beings are haphazard and unpredictable?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.90,0:03:15.24,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,We remember things the way we want to remember them and often forget what we want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.34,0:03:16.44,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,That’s being human.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.44,0:03:17.38,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,That’s normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.76,0:03:18.92,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Normal?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.06,0:03:23.66,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Yes. You dwell on things too much, Lain. All those things are normal.
